From dcc88fc2eaec2e02e1a51d0cb85826cb15dd3f77 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 10 Mar 2026 13:33:04 +0530
Subject: [PATCH 4/4] net: ethernet: tc956x: add missing check for
 CONFIG_PCI_IOV

Resolve the following compilation error for configs where PCI_IOV is
disabled:
- | tc956xmac_main.c: In function 'tc956xmac_dvr_probe':
- | tc956xmac_main.c:15472:15: error: 'struct tc956xmac_priv' has no
member named 'sriov_enabled'; did you mean 'rxp_enabled'?
- | 15472 |         priv->sriov_enabled = res->sriov_enabled;

Upstream-Status: Pending [follow up with Toshiba]
Signed-off-by: Mohd Ayaan Anwar <mohd.anwar@oss.qualcomm.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956xmac_main.c | 2 ++
 1 file changed, 2 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956xmac_main.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956xmac_main.c
index 0bcc0a9..aea82b7 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956xmac_main.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/toshiba/tc956x/tc956xmac_main.c
@@ -15469,8 +15469,10 @@ int tc956xmac_vf_dvr_probe(struct device *device,
 	priv->pause = pause;
 	priv->plat = plat_dat;
 #ifdef TC956X_SRIOV_PF
+#ifdef CONFIG_PCI_IOV
 	priv->sriov_enabled = res->sriov_enabled;
 #endif
+#endif
 #ifdef TC956X
 	priv->tc956x_SFR_pci_base_addr = res->tc956x_SFR_pci_base_addr;
 	priv->tc956x_SRAM_pci_base_addr = res->tc956x_SRAM_pci_base_addr;
-- 
2.34.1

